The course is a practical training of translating professional texts from the second foreign language into Estonian.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the skills of translating LSP-texts on business from the foreign language into Estonian. During the seminars, students  learn different translation strategies and methods for achieving the aim of the translation task. Students enhance their command of  terminology in Estonian as well as in the foreign language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the course you have acquired the skills of  - analysis of LSP-texts on business in the foreign language and translating these texts into Estonian, - using the appropriate terminology, - choosing the appropriate translation strategy for carrying out the translation task, - finding the necessary information for translation and using the appropriate sources as well as justifying your translation choices, - applying the necessary digital competences, - solving translation problems individually and as a member of a team, managing your time accordingly.
